mutant: m040_live_op_drop_escalated_whole_event
target: internal/ingest/live/events.go
failure-mode: |
  convertCommit escalates a per-op validation drop to a whole-event
  InvalidEventError, killing the benign sibling ops that share the
  commit. Models the wrong-severity class: the survivors contract says
  drop the op, keep siblings; this drops everything, silently losing
  well-formed records whenever any op in a commit is spec-invalid.
expected-detection: |
  Every #204 adversarial op commit carries a benign sibling the expected
  event log requires archived; whole-event escalation makes the sibling
  a missing expected row in the steady-state multiset compare (and the
  cursor-gap guard sees an unexempted lost cursor). Default tier.
expected-tier: default
tiers: default,stress

